The paper deals with the problem of ranking search results in digital archives using semantic information and metadata. This problem is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL), as well as to machine learning (cs.DL) and databases (cs.DB) which are likely to be used in the proposed ranking model. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of entities, which are often studied in the context of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
